# =============================================================================
# MonAI — .gitignore
#
# Keep the public repo focused on useful documents: design, formalisation,
# security, operations, simulator source code, and the curated site assets.
# Everything else (caches, large run outputs, internal working audits, local
# backups) stays out.
# =============================================================================

# --- Python tooling ---------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.Python
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/

# --- Jupyter ----------------------------------------------------------------
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- Virtual environments ---------------------------------------------------
venv/
env/
.venv/

# --- OS / editor metadata ---------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# --- Secrets ----------------------------------------------------------------
.env
*.key
secrets.json

# --- Temporary / backup files -----------------------------------------------
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak

# --- Claude Code local state ------------------------------------------------
# Session/context state private to this machine. Not for publication.
# Leading slash anchors to repo root so the root CLAUDE.md is ignored but
# `site-v2/CLAUDE.md` (Next.js AGENTS.md pointer) stays tracked.
.claude/
/CLAUDE.md

# --- Internal working audits (kept out of publication) ---------------------
# All operations/ audit files are internal QA artifacts used to gate the
# release. They may contain sensitive pre-publication detail, internal
# arbitration trace, or working-state context that should not ship.
operations/08-audit-pre-publication.md
operations/09-audit-final-publication.md
operations/09-audit-coherence-papers.md

# --- Local site backup ------------------------------------------------------
# Legacy snapshot of site/ kept locally for safety. The live `site/` folder
# is the one that ships.
site.backup/
site.zip

# --- Simulator run outputs --------------------------------------------------
# 170+ result folders, large CSVs, calibration scratch. Reproducible by
# running the scenarios. The curated figures consumed by the published
# `site/` and by the new Next.js landing live in `site/figures/` and are
# committed.
simulateur/results/
